100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 10, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing measures to enhance international security amid rising tensions in Europe. In the United States, a significant storm swept across the Midwest, causing disruptions and challenging the ongoing recovery from the recent economic downturn. Additionally, the trial of the notorious gangster Al Capone continued to capture public attention, highlighting the ongoing struggle against organized crime in American cities.
